    <name>Buckbarrow, Seatallan and Middle Fell</name>
    <bounds minlat="54.4367035" minlon="-3.3435563" maxlat="54.4688274" maxlon="-3.3113644" />
  </metadata>
  <rte>
    <name>Buckbarrow, Seatallan and Middle Fell</name>
    <desc>Driving into Wasdale is a special experience with high fells, including England's highest mountain, providing a dramatic backdrop to England's deepest lake, Wast Water. This Lake District circular walk connects three 'Wainwrights' to form a varied horseshoe route, which, although not heading for major peaks, offers some superb mountain panoramas for much of the way.</desc>
	<author>Copyright Walking Britain</author>
	<url>www.walkingbritain.co.uk/walk-1303-description</url>
	<urlname>Walk - Buckbarrow, Seatallan and Middle Fell</urlname>
      
